<statement>
<p>Which of the following is largest amount (rather than largest percent)? </p>
<p><ol style="list-style-type:upper-alpha"><li>35<percent/> of 161</li> 
<li>1<percent/> of 2717</li> 
<li>82<percent/> of 73</li> 
</ol></p>


</statement>
<solution>
<p><ul><li>C: 82<percent/> of 73</li></ul></p><p>We must first calculate (or at least approximate) each value.</p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{82}\%\cdot{73}={59.86}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{35}\%\cdot{161}={56.35}</m></p>
<p>
  <m>\displaystyle{1}\%\cdot{2717}={27.17}</m></p>
<p>From these calculations we see that 82<percent/> of 73 is the largest.</p>

</solution>
